<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-12-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-12-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="465" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Willis</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 11.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                        the United States.</hi><lb/><hi rend="italic">Honolulu,
                                        Hawaiian Islands</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-12-14"><hi rend="italic">December 14, 1893</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The day set apart by the Presidents
                            proclamation as a day of thanksgiving was appropriately observed by the
                            American citizens residing in Honolulu. The customary newspaper notices
                            from the U. S. legation were inserted and services were held in the
                            Central Union and St. Andrew’s churches.</p>
                        <p>Very respectfully,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Albert S.
                            Willis.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>